wiki.summary: On “Cupid - Twin Version”, FIFTY FIFTY find theirselves in a love situation as they think Cupid is a dumb lie, while they still thirst for a lover. The song gives the listener the perfect Valentines feel with a taste of light dance-pop. Additionally, this is the second track to their single-album of the same name. The song is the “twin version” of “Cupid” due to being sang only by members Aran and Sio and the change of lyrics—which is that this song is the English version, and the other is the original, with Korean lyrics. Read more on Last.fm.
